{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/57013", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/57013/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/57013/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/57013/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/57013", "id": 393152958, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzOTMxNTI5NTg=", "number": 57013, "title": "New Rust 2018 macro use syntax force the need to add internal macros (if the used macro require them)", "user": {"login": "robmv", "id": 1652983, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2NTI5ODM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1652983?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/robmv", "html_url": "https://github.com/robmv", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/robmv/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/robmv/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/robmv/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/robmv/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/robmv/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/robmv/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/robmv/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/robmv/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/robmv/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2018-12-20T17:59:48Z", "updated_at": "2018-12-20T19:17:07Z", "closed_at": "2018-12-20T19:16:51Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "When adding a `use` for an external crate macro, that references other macros, the compiler force to add all internal macros, for example, using the [error-chain](https://crates.io/crates/error-chain) crate\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nuse error_chain::error_chain;\r\n\r\nerror_chain! {\r\n    foreign_links {\r\n        IO(std::io::Error);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nThe following error is shown:\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror: cannot find macro `error_chain_processing!` in this scope\r\n```\r\nThe only way to fix this is to add all macros to the macro use:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nuse error_chain::{error_chain, error_chain_processing, impl_error_chain_kind, impl_error_chain_processed, impl_extract_backtrace, ChainedError};\r\n```\r\nMany of these macros are not for external use, so this new Rust 2018 syntax makes these more verbose, exposing internal names to the crate client code. Using a wildcard like:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nuse error_chain::*\r\n```\r\nworks, but pollutes the client namespace importing everything. The old `#[macro_use]` at least only imported macros\r\n\r\nNote: Related to #25003", "closed_by": {"login": "steveklabnik", "id": 27786, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI3Nzg2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/27786?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik", "html_url": "https://github.com/steveklabnik", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/5